{
  "texts": [
    "A cloud managed by a thirdparty service provider is semi-trustworthy, i.e., stealing or tampering with user data may occur [2] and data can be leaked through malicious attacks on a cloud server [3,4].Blockchain technology possesses features such as data integrity, consistency, and a protection mechanism against alterations [5].",
    "Thus, it is difficult for malicious individuals to damage the data kept in blocks on a blockchain.",
    "Leveraging a blockchain to ensure the confidentiality and security of sensitive patient EMRs provides an advantage in terms of data integrity.",
    "However, a blockchain is not a good option for storing and processing big data fast [6,7].As a blockchain grows in size, its performance and scalability decrease, while its complexity increases.",
    "MotivationExisting studies in the literature lack adequacy in terms of the access control, storage, processing, and sharing of patient data."
  ]
}